    "summary": "Hard working team player with a specialization in the domain of Computational Fluid Dynamics (CFD), always keeping an eye for the practical.\n\n... now with Origen, expanding practices towards CO2 removal applications and support the development and delivery of environmental solutions in air (and water).\n\n\u2026 have been deeply involved in thermal industrial systems for industry as well as in the related processes as the first required steps to tackle environmental issues and address issues such as:\n\u2022 Highlight and analyse the operation of burners and related combustion chambers, of furnaces, heat and power plants, (pre-)calciners, flash-furnaces, rotary kilns, torrefaction units, municipal waste incinerator etc\u2026\n\u2022 Unearth operational inefficiencies (trouble shooting)\n\u2022 Derive/develop process design/modifications yielding to operational improvements, cost reduction, emissions control, increased throughput and reliability (maintenance)\n\u2022 Advise plants\u2019 management on process/design modifications to be carried out\n\nWithin the following fields of application:\n\u2022 Mineral processing industry (lime, cement and alumina plants) \u2013 Alternative fuels\n\u2022 Torrefaction units \u2013 Biomass furnaces\n\u2022 Industrial Heat and power plants - Pulverized fuels, biomass residues &/or blends co-firing - Slagging and fouling phenomena\n\u2022 Oil and/or gas firing furnaces in refineries and in petro-chemical applications - Sulphur recovery units\n\u2022 Municipal waste incinerators\n\u2022 Emissions characterization and quantification \u2013 NOx, SOx predictions \u2013 Reburning techniques\n\n",
